<article>
    <h1>New drops in K-pop, J-pop</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200813/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-08-13"><time>2020-08-13</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE | MUSIC</span>
        - <span role="byline">Jan Lee&#xD;&#xA;jan&#xAD;lee@sph.com.sg</span>
    </section>

    <p>1</p>
    <p>ELEC­TRONIC DANCE MU­SIC</p>
    <p>NIGHT DIVER</p>
    <p>Haruma Miura</p>
    <p>Hear it on: Spo­tify, Ap­ple Mu­sic and other mu­sic stream­ing plat­forms Watch it on: bit.ly/2PLQwZK</p>
    <p>The late Ja­panese ac­tor Haruma Miura (right) showed the world that he could dance and sing just as well as he could act with the sleek and sexy elec­tronic pop num­ber Night Diver – his sec­ond sin­gle – writ­ten and pro­duced by the pro­lific Yuki Tsu­jimura. Trag­i­cally, Miura died be­fore the re­lease – at the age of 30. This post­hu­mous track will be fol­lowed by two more later in the month, in­clud­ing a song named You & I, writ­ten and com­posed by Miura him­self.</p>
    <p>2</p>
    <p>R&B/SOUL</p>
    <p>HOLO</p>
    <p>Lee Hi</p>
    <p>Hear it on:</p>
    <p>Spo­tify, Ap­ple Mu­sic and other mu­sic stream­ing plat­forms</p>
    <p>Watch it on: bit.ly/2PL­drEw</p>
    <p>In South Korean soloist Lee Hi’s (above) first mu­si­cal re­lease since her de­par­ture from her pre­vi­ous man­age­ment agency YG Entertainm­ent, the songstress sings about learn­ing to love and value her­self. Her soul­ful vo­cals shine through in Holo.</p>
    <p>3</p>
    <p>POP</p>
    <p>SONG OF THE SIRENS</p>
    <p>GFriend</p>
    <p>Hear it on: Spo­tify, Ap­ple Mu­sic and other mu­sic stream­ing plat­forms</p>
    <p>Watch it on: bit.ly/2DSGuDd</p>
    <p>South Korean sex­tet GFriend’s (above) new EP leads with Ap­ple – a dance song that sees the group tak­ing on the good and bad in fairy tales and get­ting slowly en­ticed to the dark side.</p>
    <p>4</p>
    <p>POP 1 BIL­LION VIEWS</p>
    <p>Exo-SC</p>
    <p>Hear it on: Spo­tify, Ap­ple Mu­sic and other mu­sic stream­ing plat­forms</p>
    <p>Watch it on: bit.ly/3iyGU0B</p>
    <p>The K-pop boy band Exo’s sub-unit – com­pris­ing Se­hun (above, left) and Chanyeol (above, right) – has put out a trippy, laid-back track ti­tled 1 Bil­lion Views. It has a com­fort­able beat to bob your head to, with flirty lyrics about think­ing of some­one a bil­lion times. It also fea­tures fe­male singer-song­writer Moon.</p>
    <p>5</p>
    <p>ORIG­I­NAL SOUND­TRACK</p>
    <p>WAKE UP</p>
    <p>Elaine</p>
    <p>Hear it on: Spo­tify, Ap­ple Mu­sic and other mu­sic stream­ing plat­forms</p>
    <p>Watch it on: bit.ly/3aokOen</p>
    <p>Wake up, the fully English sound­track to the ro­mance drama It’s Okay To Not Be Okay, is a de­par­ture from the usual bal­lads that ac­com­pany K-dra­mas. The cheeky song by Korean-Amer­i­can artist Elaine en­cour­ages one to let go of bur­dens and be free.</p>
    <p>6</p>
    <p>R&B</p>
    <p>SHE GOT IT</p>
    <p>Bibi</p>
    <p>Hear it on: Spo­tify, Ap­ple Mu­sic and other mu­sic stream­ing plat­forms Watch it on: bit.ly/2Cp4aik</p>
    <p>South Korean mu­si­cian Bibi’s edgy, cool re­lease</p>
    <p>She Got It – also known as Cig­a­rette And Con­dom – is ir­rev­er­ent, sexy fun. Her sul­try drawl and the re­bel­lious at­ti­tude to sex and ro­mance make this a stand­out K-pop track in a mu­sic in­dus­try where sen­si­bil­i­ties re­main con­ser­va­tive.</p>
    <p>7</p>
    <p>POP</p>
    <p>STRAY SHEEP</p>
    <p>Ken­shi Yonezu</p>
    <p>Hear it on: Spo­tify, Ap­ple Mu­sic and other mu­sic stream­ing plat­forms Watch it on: bit.ly/2XShFOQ</p>
    <p>Pop­u­lar Ja­panese singer-song­writer Ken­shi Yonezu’s much-awaited fifth al­bum is fi­nally here af­ter three years. While it in­cludes pre­vi­ously re­leased hit sin­gles like Lemon (2018), the new songs are the high­lights. The light Latino in­flu­ences of Cam­panella and the funky Kan­den, which fea­tures a range of in­stru­ments, show­case the singer’s ver­sa­til­ity.</p>
    <p>8</p>
    <p>POP/R&B</p>
    <p>MY LIT­TLE THOUGHT EP. 01</p>
    <p>San­deul (B1A4)</p>
    <p>Hear it on: Spo­tify, Ap­ple Mu­sic and other mu­sic stream­ing plat­forms Watch it on: bit.ly/31XpUdZ</p>
    <p>South Korean boy band B1A4’s vo­cal­ist San­deul’s mini-al­bum is a com­fort­ing lis­ten. His sooth­ing vo­cals and the re­lax­ing melody of the songs – espe­cially in the lead track Sum­mer Day Sum­mer Night, which tells of a bud­ding ro­mance – make the al­bum feel like a cool breeze.</p>
    <p>9</p>
    <p>ELEC­TRO-POP 2 KIDS</p>
    <p>Taemin</p>
    <p>Hear it on: Spo­tify, Ap­ple Mu­sic and other mu­sic stream­ing plat­forms</p>
    <p>Watch it on: bit.ly/3gNHS8U</p>
    <p>Ever since the sexy an­drog­y­nous charm of Move (2017) and Want (2019), fans have been ex­cit­edly wait­ing for Taemin’s (left) next re­lease.</p>
    <p>The Shi­nee mem­ber’s new track 2 Kids is more in­tro­spec­tive and tells the story of “two kids” and the re­gret one has for a past love.</p>
    <p>Though the mu­sic video is not heavy on chore­og­ra­phy, the singer’s sig­na­ture dance moves are still in­cor­po­rated.</p>
    <p>10</p>
    <p>POP</p>
    <p>IN THE SUM­MER</p>
    <p>Arashi</p>
    <p>Hear it on: Spo­tify, Ap­ple Mu­sic and other mu­sic stream­ing plat­forms Watch it on: bit.ly/2XPLLTm</p>
    <p>The J-pop boy band (left) have re­leased their first orig­i­nal mu­sic of the year – the breezy sea­sonal track In The Sum­mer. It has an elec­tronic dance mu­sic vibe and more English lyrics than the five-man group’s usual Ja­panese of­fer­ings.</p>

